A DealCloud MCP server is a standardized connector that allows AI agents to interact directly with your DealCloud CRM data [1][2]. It enables AI to retrieve and act on information like deals, relationships, and pipelines without requiring custom integration development [3][1].

Currently, there is no generic, public-use DealCloud MCP server. Instead, integration is handled through specific enterprise platforms:

Intapp offers an MCP server as part of its Celeste architecture, which is in limited release [3]. It requires enrollment in their guided implementation program to manage security and ethical wall compliance [3].

Louisa AI provides an MCP server that integrates DealCloud with AI clients like Claude, Cursor, and Microsoft Copilot to surface relationship graphs and opportunity data [4].

Because these servers provide access to sensitive business data, they must be configured by your firm's administrators to ensure proper authentication and compliance [3][5][4]. Implementation typically involves adding a configuration block to your AI client, such as Claude for Desktop, provided by your vendor [3][4]:

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "your-server-name": {
      "url": "<provided by vendor>",
      "transport": "http",
      "auth": {
        "type": "oauth2",
        "client_id": "<provided by vendor>"
      }
    }
  }
}
```
